	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 11th 11:21 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I can confirm the following:<br><br>The item needed which drops from Gorenaire is the White Dragonscale Hide.<br><br>You need a Black Sapphire Platinum Necklace and a Diamond Platinum Wedding Ring. Both items need to be made by a jeweller and in both cases, the platinum bars need to be enchanted before combining with the gems.<br><br>Take your hide, necklace and ring and head to the Rathe Mountains. As you zone in from Lake Rathetear, just to your left is a Gypsy Camp. Turn left at the gypsy camp and just run around the hill behind the camp. The first building you come to is a single hut. Inside this hut is Kerak Dragonforge (who is hiding behind the door and can't be seem unless you go right in the building). The question/answer routine seems to be broken, but just hand him your 3 items together to receive the cloak.<br><br>With the added Extended Damage 3 property, this is now a godly item for a wizard. I can confirm that it increases all DD spells, INCLUDING Manaburn.<br><br>Master Foneldar Fyreheart<br>Sorcerer of Avalon on the Stormhammer server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
